Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.60,0:01:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A large landing fleet led by General MacArthur was approaching Leyte Island, in the Philippines.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.46,0:01:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,On October 20th, 1944, prior to the start of landing, General MacArthur commanded on board the cruiser Nashville.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.01,0:02:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He was impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been two years and seven months since he said goodbye to his subordinates on the Bataan Peninsula
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.40,0:02:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and Filipino citizens on March 11th, 1942,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the midst of starvation and Japanese shells, leaving by saying, "I shall return".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.40,0:02:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I am General MacArthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.98,0:02:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Filipino citizens, I came back. With the blessing of God. {Seems an awefully brief translation for the length of audio.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.23,0:02:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,From this point onward, the Japanese forces, which discovered the American fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to challenge them with a decisive battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.32,0:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Sho-Ichi-go, which was prepared two months ago, was launched and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kurita fleet of the combined fleet was in the Leyte Gulf. It was decided to destroy the American convoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Leyte Gulf (Part 1) (Episode 21)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.08,0:03:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2nd Fleet of Kurita, which was based in Brunei Bay in Borneo,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.86,0:03:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,had a strategy meeting with each captain on the 25th regarding
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.10,0:03:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the order of Commander-in-Chief Toyeda, who had entered Leyte Gulf.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.12,0:03:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As you may already know, in this operation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.66,0:03:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Third Fleet led by Vice Admiral Ozawa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.22,0:03:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,, will be dispatched in this direction as a decoy for the aircraft carrier Zuikaku and other air squadrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.22,0:03:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Its goal is to attract the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.26,0:03:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the Fifth Fleet, led by Vice Admiral Shima,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will join our Second Fleet at the entrance to Leyte Gulf via the Suriagao Strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,With our Kurita fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.55,0:03:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the First Night Battle Unit led by Commander Kurita will rush into Leyte Gulf via the San Bernardino Strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.56,0:04:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Second Night Warfare unit will invade from the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.95,0:04:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that. However, what are we going to use to attack these transport ships?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.23,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For that matter, an air raid via aircraft carrier is sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.47,0:04:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is command thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We should make the first goal the destruction of the enemy's main force, but nevertheless,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.22,0:04:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we use to attack this convoy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think we don't need the Second Fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.80,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A decisive fleet battle is our mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if the enemy's capital ships appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it is understood that you will stop attacking the convoy and attack their capital ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.08,0:04:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the luxury of fighting a flashy battle is no longer allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.58,0:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think Captain Musashi? You have been silent for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.36,0:04:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I disagree with everyone's opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:05:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to say this, especially given our 46 cm cannons,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think the age of decisive fleet battles ended with the Russo-Japanese War.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is the time when everything is decided by decisive air battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.33,0:05:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than sticking to the honor of the decisive fleet battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.22,0:05:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,our problem is how to reduce the damage we take and increase our attack power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.77,0:05:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's more problematic to go naked into Leyte Gulf without having a single plane,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.25,0:05:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,even though the enemy's MTF has mastered carrier operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.05,0:05:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You said honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.86,0:05:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.49,0:05:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ignoring the Navy's tradition?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.78,0:05:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do with such a weak will?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.36,0:05:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINES
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, we got some great news.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.92,0:05:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that they have loaded a 250 kg bomb into the Zero and formed a Kamikaze corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:06:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With a one-way deadly attack we do not need to be afraid of 100 aircraft carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.98,0:06:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The discussions of the captains who object to the decisive fleet battle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have been put to an end by the report of the Kamikaze corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General Inoguchi, the captain of the battleship Musashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was worried about the idea of a decisive fleet battle ominously clinging to his colleague's and his boss's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.67,0:06:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,hmmm {Maybe just get rid of this? Present in HA subs.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.35,0:06:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The refueling work is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.39,0:06:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, I'm going to sortie without air cover, but the enemy will definitely come to raid us by air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.27,0:06:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not get a decisive fleet battle. We will definitely suffer great damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.39,0:06:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.06,0:07:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but I have to go because it's an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.95,0:07:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, I can only think of the Musashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do as the deputy director?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow their instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.41,0:07:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do my best within my authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.34,0:07:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing I can do is reduce the damage to the Second Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.14,0:07:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear about the Kamikaze corps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.08,0:07:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah They can't return.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.30,0:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't return.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.54,0:07:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Deputy Director Kato.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.20,0:07:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately paint the hull and deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this painting order mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's late. Do it quicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sergeant Arakawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.54,0:08:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It is only us doing this painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why only us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.19,0:08:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't dally, do it quickly. Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.28,0:08:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain is a fourth generation officer and the deputy captain is a second generation officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,4(shi) and 2(ni) are shinishozoku (burial clothes)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.07,0:08:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of face is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I think military personnel are always dressed for death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.09,0:08:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone needs to change their dress today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain is already prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:09:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, do it fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This Musashi is an unsinkable battleship, she is designed to run even if she receives hits from five or six torpedoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At 8:00 am on October 22nd, 1944, out of Brunei Bay, a fleet of 27 ships, including the main forces of the Kurita fleet:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.57,0:09:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Musashino, Yamato, and Nagato, sailed around the southern tip of the Mindoro Island from the west side of Palawan
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.16,0:09:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They went through the San Bernardino Strait to Leyte Gulf along the eastern coast of Samar Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.41,0:09:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Their mission would take them about 1900 kms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.40,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander-in-Chief of the combined Fleet, Toyeda, sent a telegram encouraging a decisive battle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Kurita fleet passed off Palawan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.98,0:10:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Renew your preparedness here, fight with purpose, and annihilate your strong enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as early as it was, the American submarines Dace and Darter spotted the Japanese fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.54,0:10:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, can you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.19,0:10:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a cruiser?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.98,0:10:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Cruisers and destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.38,0:10:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.18,0:10:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.08,0:10:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Really beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.99,0:10:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see battleships?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What a waste to sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.56,0:11:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with the first cruiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.78,0:11:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.91,0:11:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.92,0:11:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.04,0:11:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's a nice sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Full starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.85,0:11:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.60,0:11:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao was hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.60,0:11:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's depth charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.08,0:11:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a depth charge. We hit them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.66,0:11:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,4, 5, and 6 hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.85,0:12:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maya was also killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to rescue the survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.27,0:12:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Early though it was for the Kurita fleet, the heavy cruiser Atago, and Maya
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.67,0:12:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,were lost and Takao was also wrecked as Captain Inoguchi had said would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.78,0:12:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, many difficulties were expected as they went.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A report from an American search aircraft that discovered the Japanese fleet off the southern tip of Mindoro
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately reached Admiral Halsey, who is in direct command on the carrier Lexington.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.30,0:13:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 8:37 am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack! There is only the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.32,0:13:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At the command of General Halsey, the full-scale Battle of Leyte Gulf has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.95,0:13:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,From Bogan's aircraft carriers: Intrepid, Cabot, and Independence, {Yes real guy https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerald_F._Bogan}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.30,0:13:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,31 fighters, 16 torpedo bombers, and 12 dive bombers were launched in search of the Kurita fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:14:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time, but your opponent will not be a warship, but be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.62,0:14:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the first time that the world's largest cannon was to be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.10,0:14:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Every naval watcher's eyes were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I am ready. Can you work?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The burial clothing is also completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Burial clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.03,0:14:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain is fourth generation, I am second generation, so 42 (Shi-ni).
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.89,0:15:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The soldiers all know the captain's feelings as the lead ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.32,0:15:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In case of emergency, try to save as many lives as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy carrier-based aircraft!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.87,0:15:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right 95 degrees on the horizon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the duel of Ganryujima in the Showa era, Kojiro was the sun. {I think he is talking about https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miyamoto_Musashi#Duel_with_Sasaki_Kojir%C5%8D}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:15:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't shoot the main guns,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop firing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.22,0:16:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain amount of impact from the 46 cm gun was predicted,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but the actual impact was so great that other armaments could no longer be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a miscalculation of the Navy's traditional fleet battle principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Musashi did not lose its function at all even if though it was hit by a torpedo bomber and strafed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.02,0:16:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The confident appearance of the unsinkable ship Musashi, who shrugged off a single torpedo hit,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.85,0:16:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,conversely awakened the fighting spirit of the American pilots who began to clearly aim for Musashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.92,0:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is targeting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.86,0:17:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They are coming more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.47,0:17:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,1:30 pm. A third group of 65 aircraft and then a fourth group of 25 aircraft attacked the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.04,0:17:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Musashi, who had no friendly air cover,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.82,0:17:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,was hit by five torpedoes and five more bombs in these concentrated attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Inoguchi was also seriously injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, at 2:00 pm Musashi, whose speed dropped to 6 knots, left the battle line.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy comes another time the ship will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.92,0:17:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. No more ammunition. There are no people to man the guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.88,0:17:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What about food?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.43,0:17:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a meal there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.29,0:17:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to eat. {HA: "Attach to Battle food"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.50,0:17:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.87,0:17:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I had only eaten half of breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well made, despite the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.86,0:17:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even make rice balls because there are no people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok then for me to eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.74,0:18:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't fight if I am hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.00,0:18:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.89,0:18:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey it's rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.88,0:18:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,After all it is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.71,0:18:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I couldn't eat anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.38,0:18:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.34,0:18:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is it a midnight snack?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.80,0:18:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Our lives won't last until night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.54,0:18:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still want to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:19:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.06,0:19:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I said something bad earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.64,0:19:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No more, not even for Musashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the order to leave the ship has been issued yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.09,0:19:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a violation of military law if you leave the ship before the order is issued.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Soldier Wakamizu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.59,0:19:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Sugano.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.17,0:20:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather the surviving anti-aircraft gunners on the back deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.62,0:20:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunners, gather on the rear deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that grabbed the mind of Captain Sugano, the commander of the 7th Squad of anti-aircraft gunners?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time he wanted to help as many living soldiers as possible on the Musashi, who had lost her function,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.46,0:20:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the delay in ordering the crew to leave the ship from the captain? {HA: it was only a matter of time before the order to leave the ship came from the top. }
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.30,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's struggle today was brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Really hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Without you more would have been killed and injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand for anyone to be hurt anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.42,0:20:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Musashi will soon sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.76,0:20:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,However, no order to leave the ship has been issued yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is shameful for military personnel to leave the ship without an abandon ship order, it is against military law.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,However, no more can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.68,0:20:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I take responsibility for the anti-aircraft crews.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.78,0:21:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone find something suitable and abandon ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This decision saved many lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.58,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,May I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.06,0:21:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I issued an order to leave the ship at my own discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.48,0:21:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Please punish me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.18,0:21:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I missed my chance while writing a suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.27,0:21:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You took initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.77,0:21:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.90,0:21:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have a suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Deputy Director Kato, I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.76,0:22:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys should go too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.24,0:22:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave you be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.73,0:22:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I will also accompany you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.04,0:22:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All that remains here will be the casualties and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My lack of effort...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.25,0:22:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.84,0:22:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.22,0:22:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The proper decision of Captain Sugano, a mid-level officer, saved the lives of many soldiers in a timely manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.28,0:23:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, Musashi, who was proud of her unsinkability, sank.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.40,0:23:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At the expense of the decisive fleet battle principle, he could not fulfill his mission as a battleship, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.66,0:23:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,With the decision of Major General Inoguchi,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.57,0:23:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who became the admiral in charge, and kept the damage to the entire fleet small,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.67,0:23:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the will of the senior Captain Sugano's order to leave the ship, which saved many lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.54,0:23:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is still being reported as a decision of the mid-level officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.78,0:23:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, like the late Musashi, her captain, Major General Inoguchi, made a splendid sacrifice.
